==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /mɔː(r)dənt/

====Homophones====
*[[mordent]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Biting; [[caustic]]; sarcastic; [[keen]]; [[severe]].
# Serving to fix colors when [[dye]]ing.
#*'''1964''', ''In dyeing two mediums are required, the colouring matter and the '''mordant''' which fixes the dye in the wool.''  &mdash; L.F. Salzman, ''English Industries of the Middle Ages'', p. 208.

====Translations====
{{rfc-trans}}
*Finnish: [[pureva]] (1), [[julma]] (1), [[pisteliäs]] (1), [[puretin]]- (2, ''in compounds'')

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# Any substance used to [[facilitate]] the [[fixing]] of a [[dye]] to a [[fibre]]; usually a [[metallic]] compound which reacts with the dye using [[chelation]].

